radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild subsegmental atelectasis at the lung bases; inflammatory change in the right lower quadrant with a dilated appendix showing wall thickening and enlargement up to 13 mm; an obstructing appendicolith; reactive stranding and lymph node enlargement; unremarkable liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, ureters; collapsed sigmoid colon; normal gallbladder; unremarkable osseous structures except for degenerative change at L5-S1 with mild broad-based disc bulge and endplate change.
